<TITLE> President, CA host Eid get-together </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 2 (bdnews24.com)  The president and chief adviser exchanged Eid greetings on Thursday with the diplomats, distinguished personalities and people from across the social spectrum. President Iajuddin Ahmed accompanied by his wife Anwara Begum exchanged Eid pleasantries with the diplomats first from 9:30 and then with eminent citizens and government officials half an hour later at the Bangabhaban. Chief adviser Fakhruddin Ahmed exchanged greetings with the diplomats and his interim cabinet colleagues from 11am. He then saw top businessmen, leaders of professional organisations, senior journalists and other visitors at his residence at Sher-e-Bangla Nagar until midday. The visitors to the Bangabhaban and the Chief Adviser's residence were all treated to sweet dishes and delicacies on the occasion. Congregations galore Thousands of Eid congregations were held across the country and capital Dhaka alone saw a total of 360 hosted by Dhaka City Corporation in the 90 wards While many of the world's Muslims celebrated Eid as early as Tuesday, Bangladeshi Muslims observed 30 full days of fasting this year as in the last two years. The main Eid congregation in Dhaka was being held at the National Eidgah premises from 8:30am, led by Khatib of the Baitul Mukarram National Mosque, Mufti Mohammad Nooruddin. Five separate congregations were held at the Baitul Mokarram National Mosque, at 7:30am, 8:30am, 9:30am, 10:30am and the last at 11:15am. DCC held four congregations in each of Dhaka's 90 wards to make a total of 360 gatherings. Chittagong hosted 221 congregations. The city corporation's two main congregations were held at Jamiatul Falah National Mosque premises at 8:30am and 9:30am. Chittagong Central Eid Congregations Committee hosted its main congregation at the city's MA Aziz Stadium. In Rajshahi, the main congregation was held at Shah Mokhdum Central Eidgah Maidan and Barisal's main congregation at Hemayet Uddin Central Eidgah Maidan. In Sylhet, the main Eid congregation was held at the city's Shahi Eidgah Maidan. In Khulna, the main Eid congregation was at the premises of the Khulna Circuit House. Illuminations went up on civic buildings across the country on the eve of Eid-ul-Fitr, marking the end of Ramadan, as people made ready for the day's festivities. Dhaka's major thoroughfares were bedecked with Eid Mubarak messages in Bangla and Arabic. President Iajuddin Ahmed and chief adviser Fakhruddin Ahmed in separate messages greeted the nation on the eve of Eid. "The appeal of Eid-ul-Fitr is eternal in establishing a friendly and peaceful society," the president said. "I hope the great lesson of Eid-ul-Fitr will prompt our national development and advancement." Fakhruddin also spoke of peace: "The holy Eid gives us an example of peace, unity and fraternity." "I call upon all to realise the significant message of Eid-ul-Fitr and implement it in every sphere of individual, social and national life." Political leaders also delivered Eid messages to their parties, supporters and the nation. As homes across the country prepared for the Thursday's celebrations, special arrangements were also made for Eid meals in hospitals, prisons and orphanages. bdnews24.com/sm/su/rah/bd/1251hours bdne
